25 whether the withdrawal was a qualified withdrawal or a nonqualified
26 withdrawal under K.S.A. 75-640 et seq., and amendments thereto. Such
27 documentation and information shall be submitted to the treasurer in the
28 manner and form required by the treasurer on or before a deadline
29 established by the treasurer and specified in the notice. If the participant
30 does not timely respond to the notice of the audit, the audited withdrawal
31 shall be conclusively presumed to be a nonqualified withdrawal. If the
32 participant does not timely respond to the notice of audit or the treasurer
33 otherwise determines that the audited withdrawal was a nonqualified
34 withdrawal, then the treasurer shall provide notice thereof to the Kansas
35 department of revenue or other appropriate taxing authorities as
36 determined by the treasurer and the participant.
37 (3) The treasurer's determination that a withdrawal is a nonqualified
38 withdrawal under K.S.A. 75-640 et seq., and amendments thereto, shall be
39 conclusive for the purposes of this act, absent manifest error.
40 (4) If the treasurer determines that the audited withdrawal was a
41 nonqualified withdrawal under K.S.A. 75-640 et seq., and amendments
42 thereto, then the participant shall refund the matching portion of the
43 withdrawal by paying such portion to the treasurer, on payment terms

